HEADWORD: Interpenetrative
<hw>In`ter*pen"e*tra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Penetrating among or between other substances; penetrating each the
other; mutually penetrative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

